============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is DNA?
A1: DNA (deoxyribonucleic acid) is a double helix molecule
     that carries genetic information. It consists of base
     pairs: adenine-thymine and guanine-cytosine.

Q2: What is the periodic table?
A2: The periodic table organizes 118 elements by atomic
     number. Elements in the same column share chemical
     properties. Rows are periods; columns are groups.

Q3: What is artificial intelligence?
A3: AI is the simulation of human intelligence by machines,
     including learning, reasoning, and problem-solving.
     Types: narrow AI (specific tasks) and general AI
     (human-level across domains).

Q4: What is capitalism?
A4: Capitalism is an economic system where private
     individuals own the means of production and markets
     determine prices and production through supply and
     demand.

Q5: What is the Big Bang?
A5: The Big Bang theory states the universe began from an
     extremely hot, dense point approximately 13.8 billion
     years ago and has been expanding ever since.

